    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "For this. \r\nWhen the CLI params select a known testnet, such as medalla or altona, this function gets called: https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/common/eth2_testnet_config/src/lib.rs#L79\r\nAnd it returns the configuration struct for either testnet. \r\n\r\nCurrently it obtains it from the downloaded version which happens when this crate gets built, see the build script: https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/common/eth2_testnet_config/build.rs\r\n\r\nThis issue, should add the required configuration files directly into the repo but in compressed form. The build script should then only decompress the compressed files rather than download them from githubusercontent.",
